0a8755f8e2d834eff6a54714ecc7d75f9932e845df35f8b59bc52a7cfe6e8b37.

Layout notes:
 - rnnoise_data.{c,h} are the upstream rnnoise_data_little.{c,h} (the "little"
   model) renamed, so rnn.c picks the small built-in weights: the plugin input
   is 8/16 kHz telephony upsampled to 48 kHz, where the big model's extra
   capacity above 4/8 kHz buys nothing.
 - The x86 RTCD sources are intentionally not vendored; without
   RNN_ENABLE_X86_RTCD the generic C kernels (plus NEON via vec_neon.h on
   ARM) are used.
 - The 8/16 kHz <-> 48 kHz polyphase resampling lives in ../rn_denoise.c,
   not in the vendored tree.
